57. What is primary structure
Answers: A. Primary structure is that structure which contributes significantly to carrying flight, ground and pressurization loads.
B. Primary structure is that structure which carries only air or inertial loads generated on or within the secondary structure.
C. Primary structure is that structure which contributes significantly to carrying flight and pressurization loads

Questions.QuestionString: 58. Which is correct about “safe-life” design principle?
Answers: A. The safe-life design principle requires that major structural elements be replaced after a fixed number of flight cycles.
B. These parts can be repaired or refurbished to extend the components life
C. This method relies upon a duplication of certain structural members to ensure that if one member failed, the other would assume the load of the failed member.
